      <p class="uppercase tracking-wide text-xs font-semibold mb-2" style="color: #c44a08;">Technology 05</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">IntelliFire: connected controls</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-10 items-start">
        <div>
          <p class="text-lg text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">IntelliFire is Heat & Glo's smart control platform, integrating the fireplace's ignition and flame-height controls with smartphone and smart-home systems. The RC400 remote, the wall-switch option, and the IntelliFire app each connect to the same underlying control system.</p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-6 mb-2">What the system controls</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">IntelliFire-equipped fireplaces can be turned on and off, have flame height adjusted, and be set to a schedule, all from a remote, a wall switch, or a smartphone app. Compatible units also integrate with Google Home and Amazon Alexa, allowing voice-command operation.</p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-6 mb-2">Why the control system matters as much as the flame</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">A fireplace that requires walking to it to turn it on or adjust it gets used less than one that responds to a voice command or a phone tap. Usage frequency affects how a homeowner values the purchase. A fireplace that is actually used every morning of a Minnesota winter produces a different ownership experience than one used occasionally because operating it is inconvenient.</p>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">Scheduling capability also removes a common consumer concern: the fear of leaving a fireplace on unintentionally. A programmed shutoff time eliminates that worry entirely.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-4">
